positions.description:
Sophie is a policy officer handling the corporate social responsibility file in DG Enterprise & Industry. She is in charge of the conceptual policy development at EU level with regard to implementing pertinent international guidelines (UN, OECD, ISO). In this regard, she is responsible for: 
- Policy development, including the update of the EU's priorities on CSR;
- Relationships with international bodies (UN, OECD, ISO) and key stakeholders, including business and trade associations, trade unions as well as NGOs;
- Co-management of the Commission's CSR multi-stakeholder group/CSR coordination committee;
- Management of the Commission's inter-service group on CSR;  and
- Handling respective EU projects which aim at implementing CSR guidelines in EU sectors.

